-(music stops)
-MAN: We're cutting. guys.

1891
01:30:11.069 --> 01:30:14.067
All right. here's what I need.
I'm thinking...

1892
01:30:15.569 --> 01:30:17.571
...I'm gonna move the camera in
while you're up here.

1893
01:30:18.074 --> 01:30:21.205
I need to get a close-up
of you at the top.

1894
01:30:21.341 --> 01:30:23.040
so just feel the camera
as you come down.

1895
01:30:23.175 --> 01:30:25.041
-Okay.
-Okay. great. All right.

1896
01:30:25.177 --> 01:30:26.282
DIRECTOR:
Okay. everybody.

1897
01:30:26.418 --> 01:30:27.718
(grunts) Here we go.

1898
01:30:27.853 --> 01:30:30.622
What is this?
What do we got. take six?

1899
01:30:30.757 --> 01:30:32.785
-(groans quietly)
-Lucky six. Lucky six.

1900
01:30:32.921 --> 01:30:34.494
Here we go. Energy. everybody!

1901
01:30:34.630 --> 01:30:37.130
You love the Jacksons.
You love the Jacksons.

1902
01:30:37.266 --> 01:30:39.123
You love Pepsi. Let's go!

1903
01:30:39.258 --> 01:30:41.630
-WOMAN: A marker!
-(marker snaps)

1904
01:30:41.765 --> 01:30:43.061
-MAN 2: B mark!
-(marker snaps)

1905
01:30:43.197 --> 01:30:44.799
-MAN 3: C mark.
-(audience cheering)

1906
01:30:44.935 --> 01:30:46.764
-(marker snaps)
-DIRECTOR: And playback.

1907
01:30:46.900 --> 01:30:50.301
("Billie Jean" playing)

1908
01:30:53.071 --> 01:30:55.141
(fireworks explode)

1909
01:31:04.557 --> 01:31:06.058
-(music fades)
-(sizzling)

1910
01:31:06.193 --> 01:31:07.390
(muffled cheering)

1911
01:31:07.525 --> 01:31:09.721
(distorted whimpering)

1912
01:31:09.857 --> 01:31:12.257
(distorted moaning)

1913
01:31:13.467 --> 01:31:14.899
-(music resumes)
-(screaming)

1914
01:31:15.035 --> 01:31:16.260
Cut it.

1915
01:31:16.396 --> 01:31:18.104
-MAN: Put it out!
-(Michael groaning)

1916
01:31:18.239 --> 01:31:19.338
(microphone feedback)

1917
01:31:19.473 --> 01:31:21.297
-(groaning)
-TITO: Michael!

1918
01:31:21.433 --> 01:31:22.901
-(clamoring. screaming)
-(groaning)

1919
01:31:23.037 --> 01:31:25.108
-What happened?
-(moaning)

1920
01:31:25.243 --> 01:31:26.977
-BILL: Back up.
back up. back up.
-Bill. get him out of here.

1921
01:31:27.113 --> 01:31:29.443
BILL: I'm here. I'm here.
I'm here. Michael.

1922
01:31:29.578 --> 01:31:31.312
-Get him up. get him up.
-I'm here. Joker. I'm here.

1923
01:31:31.447 --> 01:31:33.210
Hey. you're gonna
be okay. okay?
You're gonna be okay.

1924
01:31:33.346 --> 01:31:34.716
BILL:
Come on. Mike. Clear a path!

1925
01:31:34.851 --> 01:31:36.953
(people screaming
and clamoring)

1926
01:31:37.956 --> 01:31:40.819
Out of my way!
Michael. I'm coming!

1927
01:31:41.322 --> 01:31:42.956
-(moans)
-Get back! Get out of my way!

1928
01:31:43.092 --> 01:31:45.499
Clear a path!
Get back! Get back!

1929
01:31:46.700 --> 01:31:49.796
Clear a path!
Move! Move. please!

1930
01:31:49.932 --> 01:31:52.501
(muffled shouting and wailing)

1931
01:31:52.637 --> 01:31:54.640
BILL:
Excuse me!

1932
01:31:55.505 --> 01:31:57.174
(whimpering)

1933
01:31:57.309 --> 01:31:59.513
♪ ♪

1934
01:32:06.912 --> 01:32:08.845
(phone ringing)

1935
01:32:08.980 --> 01:32:10.480
(Joseph exhales)

1936
01:32:11.590 --> 01:32:13.857
(continues tapping fingers)

1937
01:32:17.366 --> 01:32:19.698
(indistinct P.A. announcement)

1938
01:32:24.338 --> 01:32:26.463
Hey. Kate. come on.

1939
01:32:28.409 --> 01:32:29.774
Hey. I need to talk to you.

1940
01:32:29.909 --> 01:32:31.574
-Sir.
-I'm his father.
Joseph Jackson.

1941
01:32:31.710 --> 01:32:33.439
This is his mother. Katherine.

1942
01:32:33.574 --> 01:32:35.542
-Hi. It's good to meet you.
-Very nice to meet you.

1943
01:32:35.677 --> 01:32:36.912
Thank you.

1944
01:32:37.048 --> 01:32:38.583
Well. your son is
in stable condition.

1945
01:32:38.719 --> 01:32:40.380
-All right.
-DOCTOR: All right?

1946
01:32:40.516 --> 01:32:43.081
And. uh. we're trying to bring
his heart rate down.

1947
01:32:43.216 --> 01:32:45.086
but he's in a lot of pain.

1948
01:32:46.185 --> 01:32:47.557
Okay. When will he recover?

1949
01:32:47.692 --> 01:32:49.089
It's too soon to tell.

1950
01:32:49.225 --> 01:32:51.259
It's gonna be
a long road. all right?

1951
01:32:51.395 --> 01:32:55.096
He has third-degree burns
and substantial nerve damage.

1952
01:32:56.061 --> 01:32:57.895
JOSEPH:
Okay.

1953
01:32:58.764 --> 01:33:01.699
Do you think he'll ever be
able to perform again?

1954
01:33:01.834 --> 01:33:03.209
Ever?

1955
01:33:03.344 --> 01:33:05.073
KATHERINE:
Joseph.

1956
01:33:07.682 --> 01:33:11.347
Mr. Jackson.
your son almost died.

1957
01:33:11.482 --> 01:33:12.882
I know that.

1958
01:33:13.018 --> 01:33:14.778
Well. if that fire
had caught his clothes.

1959
01:33:14.914 --> 01:33:17.716
or burned over to his face
and eyes. he wouldn't be here.

1960
01:33:17.852 --> 01:33:19.417
I know my boy.

1961
01:33:19.553 --> 01:33:21.725
And the only thing
that's gonna heal him

1962
01:33:21.861 --> 01:33:23.454
is by getting
back on that stage.

1963
01:33:24.762 --> 01:33:26.359
That's where he lives.

1964
01:33:26.495 --> 01:33:28.098
-DOCTOR:
I understand that. sir.
-LA TOYA: Oh. my God.

1965
01:33:28.233 --> 01:33:29.568
-But it's gonna be a while.
-Do you? All right.

1966
01:33:29.704 --> 01:33:31.561
DOCTOR:
Yes. I do. But. Mr. Jackson...

1967
01:33:31.696 --> 01:33:34.931
he's gonna need
your support to get there.

1968
01:33:35.067 --> 01:33:36.808
I'm sorry.

1969
01:33:39.070 --> 01:33:40.840
(exhales)

1970
01:33:41.643 --> 01:33:43.145
WOMAN (shouting in distance):
Praying for you. Michael!

1971
01:33:43.280 --> 01:33:45.076
